Chile Stocks: Azul Azul, Cap, Cruzados, La Polar, Lan Airlines

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-06-13T22:15:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-13/chilean-stocks-azul-azul-cruzados-la-polar-and-lan-airlines.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4:08 p.m. New York time.  The Ipsa index fell 1.6 percent to 4,663.35.  Azul Azul SA (AZUL)   rose 2.2 percent to 470 pesos. The
owner of the Universidad de Chile soccer team rose after winning
the national tournament.  Cruzados SADP (CRUZADOS)  , which owns
rival team Universidad Catolica, fell 10 percent to 195 pesos
after losing the final.  Cap SA (CAP)   retreated 4.8 percent to 20,965 pesos, the
biggest fall in four months. Chile’s largest steel and iron-ore
producer fell along with industrial metal prices on signs of
lower demand from  China .  Empresas La Polar SA (LAPOLAR)   fell 11 percent to 1,430
pesos before trading was suspended. The Chilean retailer that
disclosed irregular credit practices last week dropped before
giving further guidance on loan-loss provisions.  Other retailers also fell.  Ripley Corp SA (RIPLEY)  
slumped the most in two years, sliding 4.8 percent to 580.5
pesos.  SACI Falabella (FALAB)   lost 3.3 percent to 4,881.3
pesos.  Lan Airlines SA (LAN)   retreated 1.2 percent to 12,617
pesos.  Latin America ’s largest airline by market value canceled
flights between Santiago and  Buenos Aires  on June 12 and
postponed the Sydney-Auckland-Santiago flight scheduled for
today because of an  ash cloud  from a volcanic eruption,
according to a statement posted on the company’s website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
 ethomson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
